        <i class="fa-solid fa-rotate-left fa-icon"></i>
        <p>Buyers are entitled to return policies as specified by individual sellers, which must be clearly stated on product listings. These policies vary between sellers but must comply with BookMart's minimum standards for consumer protection. Generally, new books purchased from bookstores can be returned within 7 days if they arrive damaged or do not match the description. For second-hand books from individual booksellers, return policies may be more restricted, particularly for auction purchases. BookMart provides a messaging system for buyers to discuss potential returns directly with sellers.</p>
